This project bundles / depends on the following third-party software, each
under its own license. Their copyrights and license terms are preserved.

## microlink (git submodule: microlink/)
Copyright (c) 2025-2026 Cameron Malone — MIT License.
Source: https://github.com/CamM2325/microlink
Full text: see `microlink/LICENSE`.
microlink is an independent, clean-room implementation of the Tailscale
protocol and is not affiliated with or endorsed by Tailscale Inc.

## WireGuard
WireGuard is a registered trademark of Jason A. Donenfeld.
The WireGuard protocol implementation inside microlink is based on the
public WireGuard specification. This project is not affiliated with or
endorsed by Jason A. Donenfeld or the WireGuard project.

## X25519
The X25519 elliptic curve implementation inside microlink is derived from
public-domain code by Daniel J. Bernstein. See `microlink/x25519-license.txt`.

## Tailscale
"Tailscale" is a trademark of Tailscale Inc. This project uses the name
"Tailscale" only to describe interoperability with the Tailscale service /
protocol. **This project is not affiliated with, sponsored by, or endorsed
by Tailscale Inc.** No Tailscale source code is included or copied.

## ESPHome
This project is an external component for ESPHome (https://esphome.io/),
which is licensed under the GPLv3 / MIT mix documented in the ESPHome
repository. This component does not modify or redistribute ESPHome itself;
it is loaded at build time via the `external_components` mechanism.

